    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/cpb-cou1-decision-001",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-lead",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 7 assessed credibility factors met or exceeded the required level for MRL 2. The 6 not-assessed factors are acceptable at MRL 2 per ASME V&V 40-2018 Table 1. Validation results demonstrate hemolysis index predictions within 8.1% of FDA benchmark data and RH < 1 at all operating points. The credibility evidence package supports the decision to use the CFD model for identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device.",
